 <item> <title>States Open to Charters Start Fast in &#039;Race to Top&#039;</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/states-open-charters-start-fast-race-top</link>
 <description>Emphasizing the need for additional effective education entrepreneurs to join the work of reforming America&#039;s lowest performing public schools, U.S. Secretary of Education Arne Duncan told reporters during a conference call this afternoon that states must be open to charter schools. Too much is at stake for states financially and for students academically to restrict choice and innovation.</description>
